              <td>
			  <!-- inclue current newsletter here. --->
			 
			  November 2003
 <br><br>Greetings from SimpleNet!
<p>
  This newsletter contains news and information for our Hosting
  customers. Our goal is to keep you informed of product
  changes and updates, and to help you achieve your online goals.</p>
<p>
  ---------------------------------------------------------<br>
In this issue:<br>
<br>
  1. Introducing: Miva Merchant 4.21 Shopping Cart<br>
  2. Information Partner: JimWorld.com<br>
  3. Upgrades: Dedicated IPs<br>
  4. Marketing Partner: WebRing.com<br>
  5. Using Your Site: SSL, what does it mean?<br>
6. Send Feedback!<br>
<br>
  ---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  1. Introducing: The Miva Merchant 4.21 Shopping Cart
and the SimpleNet Commerce Package</p>
<p>
  Miva Merchant allows you to build the most comprehensive,
  professional ecommerce storefront on the Internet. It includes
  modules for customer registration, shipping integration,
  inventory tracking, affiliate management, transaction processing
  and much more. Miva Merchant has a complete set of wizards
  to simplify the process of building your store, maintaining your
  product catalog, and fulfilling orders.</p>
<p>
  Miva Merchant is included in the NEW SimpleNet Commerce
  package and can be added to the S-150 and S-300 packages.</p>
<p>
  To learn more about Miva Merchant or the SimpleNet Commerce
  Package, please visit:<br>
  <a href="http://www.simplenet.com/miva_merchant.html">http://www.simplenet.com/miva_merchant.html</a><br>
<br>
  ---------------------------------------------------------<br>
2. JimWorld: An Excellent Resource for Web Site Owners<br>
<br>
  We'd like to introduce you to our partner, JimWorld. Their site,
  at JimWorld.com, contains a collection of services, tools,
  resources, and collaborative efforts, each put together by and
  for the Internet's most diverse, knowledgeable, and masterful
  community of Internet professionals. They provide excellent
  information on a wide range of topics that include Search Engine
Optimization, Marketing, Design and much more.</p>
<p><br>
  Please take the time to visit our partner, JimWorld, and sign up<br>
  to receive their information-packed Gazette:<br>
  <a href="http://www.simplenet.com/miva_merchant.html">http://www.jimworld.com</a></p>
<p><br>
  ---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  3. Does your account have a Dedicated IP?</p>
<p><br>
  A Dedicated IP Address is a number that is assigned to your web
  site account. With the growth of the Internet, it is no longer
  possible for every server and web site to have its own IP Address.
  To address this issue, many Internet Presence Providers assign
  IP Address pools to shared web servers so that they may deal
  with incoming and outgoing traffic for several web sites. At
  SimpleNet, you can still get your own IP, for just $2/month.</p>
<p>
  To obtain your Dedicated IP now, please visit your Console at:<br>
  <a href="https://secure.simplenet.com/cp/">https://secure.simplenet.com/cp/</a></p>
<p>
  ---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  4. WebRing: Bringing the Internet Together</p>
<p>
  WebRing is the best way to find great web sites, share ideas with<br>
  peers and participate in topical communities for FREE. WebRing<br>
  can be used to:<br>
  - Participate in highly focused and rich online communities<br>
  - Locate sites that are of interest to you<br>
  - Take part in the more than 3000 content specific forums</p>
<p><br>
  Perhaps your web site should belong to a ring? Try joining a Ring
  and increase traffic to your site or create a Ring and develop an
  online community.</p>
<p>
  To learn more, please visit:<br>
  <a href="http://www.webring.com">http://www.webring.com</a></p>
<p>
  ---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  5. Using Your Site: SSL, what does it mean?</p>
<p>
  SSL is an accepted standard for transferring information securely
  across the Internet. It encrypts data passed between the server
  and the browser, so that unauthorized parties cannot interpret
  sensitive, confidential or personal information, such as a phone
  number, address or credit card. The type of SSL that you use
  depends on the secure address that you'd like your customers to
  see. With Shared SSL, your secure address will be,
  https://youraccount.ssl.simplenet.com. Private SSL will change
  your secure address to, https://www.youraccount.com. In order to
  use Private SSL, you must obtain a secure server certificate.</p>
<p>
  You can add SSL to all accounts except the Starter. To add SSL
  or a secure certificate to your account, please visit your Console
  and choose &quot;Web Options.&quot;<br><br>
  <a href="https://secure.simplenet.com/cp/">https://secure.simplenet.com/cp/</a></p>
<p><br>
  ---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  6. We want to hear from you!</p>
<p><br>
  The best way for us to bring you the services that you need
  is for you to tell us what you want! Whether it be to talk about
  our support, suggest new services or just tell us that we are
  doing a great job, please use our feedback areas as often as
  you like!</p>
<p><br>
  How do you do that?<br>
  1. Reply to this email<br>
  OR<br>
  2. Use our feedback form, located...<br>
  <a href="https://secure.simplenet.com/cp/">http://www.simplenet.com/contact.html<br>
  </a><br>
---------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Thanks for reading and for being a SimpleNet customer!</p>
<p><br>
  Best wishes,<br>
  The SimpleNet Team</p>
<p><br>
  For assistance, please contact Customer Care:<br>
  <a href="http://simplenet.com/contact.html">http://simplenet.com/contact.html</a></p>
<p><br>
  SimpleNet takes your privacy seriously. To learn more,<br>
  please read our privacy policy, located at<br>
  <a href="http://www.simplenet.com/privacy.html">http://www.simplenet.com/privacy.html</a></p>
			  
             </td>
